@startuml failsafe_context_to_vcu_routing_policy_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Fail-safe Context To VCU Routing Policy Signal Flow\n(Core/CoreState context -> VCU routing / vehicle-mode publication)

participant "Core / CoreState\nboundary + fail-safe context" as Core #F4F7FB
participant "VCU\nrouting and powertrain owner" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "Backbone / vehicle-mode bus" as Bus #FFF4CC
participant "CGW / ADAS / DCM /\nother observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Routing Inputs ==

Core -> VCU : CoreState::domainBoundaryStatus\nCore::failSafeMode\nCore::emergencyContext
activate VCU
VCU -> VCU : boundaryAlive = clamp(domainBoundaryStatus)
VCU -> VCU : if failSafeMode > 0 -> RoutingPolicy = 0
VCU -> VCU : else if emergencyContext > 0 -> RoutingPolicy = 2
VCU -> VCU : else RoutingPolicy = 1
note right of VCU
Representative derived values
- RoutingPolicy
- BoundaryStatus
- CtrlAuthLevel
- VehicleMode.PowertrainState
end note

== Routing Publish ==

VCU -> Bus : frmPtGwStateMsg\n(RoutingPolicy / BoundaryStatus)
VCU -> Bus : frmVehicleModeMsg\n(PowertrainState / DriveMode)
VCU -> Bus : frmCtrlAuthMsg\n(CtrlAuthLevel)
VCU -> Obs : backbone vehicle state / powertrain visibility
note right of Obs
Representative consumers
- CGW
- ADAS
- DCM / ETHB / IBOX / SGW
- powertrain-side observers
end note
deactivate VCU

note over Core, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Boundary status, fail-safe mode, and emergency context reach VCU
2. VCU selects the routing policy and control-auth level
3. VCU publishes gateway state and vehicle-mode visibility
4. Gateway, ADAS, and diagnostics consume the routing outcome
end note

@enduml
